# Stakr - Mobile UI Focused Rules

## CRITICAL MOBILE REQUIREMENTS

- **CRITICAL**: Prioritize mobile-first design over desktop
- **CRITICAL**: All layouts must be optimized for mobile usability
- **CRITICAL**: Touch targets must be minimum 44px height/width
- **CRITICAL**: All forms must be mobile-friendly (16px font size to prevent zoom)
- **CRITICAL**: Implement proper safe area handling for notched devices
- **CRITICAL**: All navigation must work with touch gestures
- **CRITICAL**: Optimize images for mobile (WebP, responsive sizes)
- **CRITICAL**: Implement pull-to-refresh for feeds and lists
- **CRITICAL**: Use bottom navigation for primary app sections
- **CRITICAL**: All modals must be dismissible with touch gestures
- **CRITICAL**: Implement proper loading states for mobile
- **CRITICAL**: All text must be readable on small screens
- **CRITICAL**: Avoid horizontal scrolling on mobile
- **CRITICAL**: Implement proper keyboard handling for forms
- **CRITICAL**: All buttons must have proper touch feedback
- **CRITICAL**: Use native share API when available
- **CRITICAL**: Implement proper offline functionality
- **CRITICAL**: Optimize bundle size for mobile performance
- **CRITICAL**: Test on multiple screen sizes and orientations
- **CRITICAL**: Implement proper haptic feedback for interactions

## MOBILE UI PATTERNS

- Use responsive design with mobile-first breakpoints
- Implement touch-friendly button sizes (min 44px)
- Use proper spacing for touch interactions
- Implement swipe gestures for common actions
- Use bottom sheets for secondary actions
- Implement proper form validation with mobile UX
- Use skeleton loading states for better perceived performance
- Implement proper error states for mobile
- Use native mobile patterns (pull-to-refresh, infinite scroll)
- Implement proper keyboard handling
- Use proper typography scaling for mobile
- Implement proper color contrast for mobile screens
- Use proper icon sizes for touch interaction
- Implement proper animation timing for mobile
- Use proper spacing and padding for mobile layouts
